@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"
@TOC "Main"

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                           I N T R O D U C T I O N
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
 Passcode is a program in which the user has to enter a password to close 
the program and therefore continue in what her or she is doing. This 
programming would be good to keep a annoying family member messing about 
with your work, just double click on Passcode`s icon and lock up!

 Passcode requires you to enter the password and username with capital and 
lower case letters in all the right places!

   @{" Back to the Contents Page! " LINK "Main"}
@ENDNODE

