@NODE "Installation" "Installation"
@TOC "Main"

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
                           I N S T A L L A T I O N
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
 If you plan to use Passcode alot it is best to copy it to your HD or 
Workbench disk, to do this open a shell and type:-

        "Copy Nicron:Passcode-V1.0/Passcode C:"

 Now, when you want to use it you just type Passcode into the shell, or you
could Put Away the Passcode icon so you can use it from the WB screen.

 To load Passcode when you boot your computer install as above and add a 
line to your user-startup reading:-

        "C:Passcode"

    @{" Back to the Contents Page! " LINK "Main"}
